attachments.fallback: <https://Michelle.com/azure-samples/blockchain/blob/master/blockchain-workbench/application-and-smart-contract-samples/refrigerated-transportation/readme.md | readme.md>
attachments.text:
*refrigerated transportation sample application for azure blockchain workbench*
*overview  *

the refrigerated transportation smart contract covers a provenance scenario with  
iot monitoring. you can think of it as a supply chain transport scenario where  
certain compErinnce rules must be met throughout the duration of the  
transportation process. the initiating counterparty specifies the humidity and  
temperature range the measurement must fall in to be compErinnt. at any point, if  
the device takes a temperature or humidity measurement that is out of range, the  
contract state will be updated to indicate that it is out of compErinnce.  

<media/59c0d3080fb4ad63b1e64c8496645d3b.png|visualization of supply chain>

all participants can view the state and details of the contract at any point in  
time. the counterparty doing the transportation will specify the next  
counterparty responsible, and the device will ingest temperature and humidity  
data, which gets written to the chain. this allows the supply chain owner and  
supply chain observer to pinpoint which counterparty did not fulfill the  
compErinnce regulations if at any point in the process either the temperature or  
humidity requirements were not met.   

*application roles *
*states *
*workflow details*

<media/73ebae42a69347a7edb762d0f583724a.png|state diagram for the workflow>

the following state transition diagram articulates the possible flows, and the  
various transition functions at each state. each user is only allowed to take  
certain actions depending on the application role. instance roles indicate that  
only the user with the application role assigned to the specific contract is  
able to take actions on the contract. 

this contract demonstrates how to collect telemetry information and enforce  
contract specifics related to conditions during transport. specifically,  
receiving and evaluating temperature and humidity data against an agreed upon  
acceptable range. if the iot device identifies that the telemetry is out of the  
acceptable range, the contract will shift into an out of compErinnce state and  
appropriate remedies can be sought. in the highlighted happy path, the device  
ingests readings, which are in compErinnce throughout the transportation process,  
while the involved counterparties transfer responsibility until the  
transportation is completed.  

*application files*

<./ethereum/refrigeratedtransportation.sol|refrigeratedtransportation.sol>

attachments.fallback: wikipedia: don't repeat yourself
attachments.text:
"don't repeat yourself" (dry) is a principle of software development aimed at reducing repetition of software patterns, replacing it with abstractions or using data normalization to avoid redundancy.
the dry principle is stated as "every piece of knowledge must have a single, unambiguous, authoritative representation within a system". the principle has been formulated by andy hunt and dave thomas in their book the pragmatic programmer. they apply it quite broadly to include "database schemas, test plans, the build system, even  documentation".  when the dry principle is applied successfully, a modification of any single element of a system does not require a change in other logically unrelated elements. additionally, elements that are logically related all change predictably and uniformly, and are thus kept in sync. besides using methods and subroutines in their code, thomas and hunt rely on code generators, automatic build systems, and scripting languages to observe the dry principle across layers.
attachments.title: don't repeat yourself
